cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CV, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper proposes an algorithm for training neural network control policies for quadrotors to perform path following and collision avoidance maneuvers. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The algorithm uses imitation learning to produce a policy that reproduces the behavior of a supervisor. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the use of a time-free model-predictive path-following controller as a supervisor. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The control policy computes control commands directly from sensor inputs, which may include visual data. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a learning algorithm for training the control policy using a relatively small number of examples on the real quadrotor.
